<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,325,1432]" pageId="7" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,398,1369,1395]" pageId="7" pageNumber="520">DNA barcoding:</emphasis>
One specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[645,788,1370,1396]" name="South Korea" pageId="7" pageNumber="520">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<accessionNumber box="[806,934,1370,1397]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/OK501200" pageId="7" pageNumber="520">OK501200</accessionNumber>
) was sequenced, and the genetic difference between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yamanaka" authorityYear="1966" box="[251,472,1406,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Anania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albeoverbascalis">
<emphasis box="[251,472,1406,1432]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="520">A. albeoverbascalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its relative, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Denis and Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[658,817,1406,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Anania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verbascalis">
<emphasis box="[658,817,1406,1432]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="520">A. verbascalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 14%.
</paragraph>
